Kenya&rsquo;s unmanned aircraft academy drone space has received the remote operators&nbsp;certificate from the Kenya civil aviation authority for commercial drone operations. The academies Chief Executive Officer Tony Mwangi says that the landmark certification is a critical step in the use of drones to provide solutions to everyday challenges.&nbsp;The Ceo added that even though flying a drone in Kenya is legal, commercial drone operations require a pilot to obtain a remote operator certificate from the Kenya Civil Aviation Authority which authorizes an operator to carry out specified drone operations.